  "title": "Maintenance Planning Engineer (Aerospace)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>In charge of ordering of required parts necessary to carry out the inspections</li>\n  <li>In charge of timely in uploading of task cards into the ERP system</li>\n  <li>In charge of the issuing the correct supporting documentation needed by the production team to carry out the maintenance checks efficiently.</li>\n  <li>In charge of documentation and revision control with OEM and Airline Operators</li>\n  <li>Responsible in identification and availability check of required tools</li>\n  <li>Correct printing and scheduling of task cards</li>\n  <li>Hangar and Production Control Support</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Job Requirement:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Minimum Diploma in Electrical, Mechanical/Mechatronics, Manufacturing/Production, Industrial Engineering or relevant</li>\n  <li>Minimum 2 years of working experience in maintenance planning of airframe maintenance projects.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>To submit your application, please apply online to <a href=\"mailto:apply@rn-care.com\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>apply@rn-care.com </strong></a>or call +(65) <a href=\"tel:6513 5697\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>6513 5697</strong></a> for private and confidential discussion.</p>\n<p>Your interest will be treated with the strictest of confidence. We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified or contacted.</p>\n<p><strong>RN Care Pte. Ltd</strong><br>\n<strong>EA License No: 17C8900</strong></p>",
